# CODEOWNERS — automatic review requests for sensitive paths.
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Five rules: a default owner for the whole repo, plus four narrow
# rules covering the paths that most often warrant a careful review.

# 1. Default owner — every PR gets the maintainer as reviewer
*                                @JacquesGariepy

# 2. Domain logic (annotations, AI providers, kanban, profiles)
/src/                            @JacquesGariepy

# 3. Build, lint, packaging, and CI configuration
/.github/workflows/              @JacquesGariepy
/package.json                    @JacquesGariepy
/tsconfig.json                   @JacquesGariepy
/webpack.config.js               @JacquesGariepy

# 4. Public-facing legal and governance documents
/LICENSE                         @JacquesGariepy
/SECURITY.md                     @JacquesGariepy
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md              @JacquesGariepy
/CONTRIBUTING.md                 @JacquesGariepy

# 5. End-user and contributor documentation
/README.md                       @JacquesGariepy
/CHANGELOG.md                    @JacquesGariepy
/docs/                           @JacquesGariepy
